This paper focuses on developing a framework for detecting false information attacks on the Controller Area Network (CAN) bus in modern vehicles. The paper utilizes machine learning techniques such as Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) and time-series classification to detect anomalies in the CAN data traffic. Additionally, the paper proposes policies for mitigating the effect of cyber-attacks using a software-defined networking (SDN) framework. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
